  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rwanda Stunting Prevention and Reduction Programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Decrease the percentage of children under 5 years with height-for-age z-score below -2 standard deviations from a baseline of 43.6% to 32% Decrease percentage of children under 2 years with height-for-age z-score below -2 standard deviations from a baseline of 37.1% to 27.2% Increase percentage of children 6-23 months old who are fed a diverse diet from baseline of 22.9% to 50% Increase percentage of women who attended 4 or more ANC visits during their most recent pregnancy from a baseline of 41% to 55%</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project includes $55 million to reduce chronic malnutrition of children in Rwanda in 13 of the country&#x2019;s poorest and most food-insecure districts with high rates of stunting. The project that will scale up the delivery of a package of high impact nutrition-specific interventions through the community health worker platform and primary care facilities. The project will support the development and roll-out of a new national strategy to improve the visibility of stunting in Rwanda and to change behaviour.</narrative>
  </description>
